        "subject": "LU-1623 mdc: Ignore unexpected server remote acl data",
        "message": "LU-1623 mdc: Ignore unexpected server remote acl data\n\nSomethign strange is going on on the MDS that causes it to think\nclients are \"remote\" and sending them some relevant ACL data.\nNow, the clients are really surprised by such turn of events and as such\ntrigger an assertion.\n\nThe root cause is unknown and the crashes annoy people so this is\na temporary workaround patch to stop such assertion from triggering.\n\nChange-Id: I5b9e6c72fda403c51076af1bee1766851f3846b4\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
